io.smint.clapi.consumer.integration.core.configuration.models

Interface IModelStringConverter<T>

  • Type Parameters:
    T - the type of model to convert to and from a String.
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    AuthTokenJsonConverter, ModelDataJsonConverter, SyncJobDataJsonConverter

    public interface IModelStringConverter<T>
    Implementing classes convert model T to and from String.

    The representation within String is totally up to the implementation, whether it is something like XML or JSON or any other form of textual representation.

    • Method Detail

      • decode

        T decode(String encodedData)
  throws ParseException
        Parses the provided String data and converts it to an instance of T.
        Parameters:
        encodedData - the encoded model data to parse.
        Returns:
        The extracted model data or null. In case parsing fail, then an exception of ParseException is thrown. In case the parameter encodedToken is an empty string or null, then null is returned.
        Throws:
        ParseException - in case the provided text can not be converted to model data and all characters consumed. Empty String values or null values are ignored and not parsed and thus no exception is being thrown.

      • encode

        String encode(T newModelData)
       throws ParseException
        Encodes an model to a String value.
        Parameters:
        newModelData - new model data for sync with Smint.io API server, that need to be encoded.
        Returns:
        An encoded version of the token or null in case the provided parameter is null.
        Throws:
        ParseException - in case the provided model data can not be converted to a String value. Nevertheless null values are ignored and not converted and thus no exception is being thrown.
